i]]|KEN|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:19.45 '''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|2.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Peter Renner]]|NZL|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:22.95 '''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|3.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Peter Daenens]]|BEL|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:28.26 '''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|4.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Henry Marsh (athlete)|Henry Marsh]]|USA|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:29.23 '''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|5.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Colin Reitz]]|GBR|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:29.33 '''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|6.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Tommy Ekblom]]|FIN|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:29.45 '''\n|- style=\"background:#eeffee;\"\n|align=\"center\"|7.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Filippos Filippou (runner)|Filippos Filippou]]|CYP|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:30.09 '''\n|- style=\"background:#eeffee;\"\n|align=\"center\"|8.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Liam O'Brien (athlete)|Liam O'Brien]]|IRL|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:31.89 '''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|9.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Yehuda Zadok]]|ISR|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:42.28   '''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|10.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Kim Ju-ryong]]|KOR|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:43.50   '''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|11.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Albert Marie]]|SEY|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''9:32.30  '''\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[1982 European Athletics Championships \u2013 Men's 3000 metres steeplechase|1982 Men's European Championships 3000 m Steeplechase (Athens)]]\n* [[1983 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 3000 metres steeplechase|1983 Men's World Championships 3000 m Steeplechase (Helsinki)]]\n* [[Athletics at the Friendship Games \u2013 Men's 3000 metres steeplechase|1984 Men's Friendship Games 3000 m Steeplechase (Moscow)]]\n* [[1986 European Athletics Championships \u2013 Men's 3000 metres steeplechase|1986 Men's European Championships 3000 m Steeplechase (Stuttgart)]]\n* [[1987 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 3000 metres steeplechase|1987 Men's World Championships 3000 m Steeplechase (Rome)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|en}} [http://sportslion.net/track/halloffame/LA1984/LA84-steeplem.html Results]\n\n{{OlympicsSteeplechase}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Athletics At The 1984 Summer Olympics - Men's 3000 Metre Steeplechase}}\n[[Category:Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics| 1]]\n[[Category:Steeplechase at the Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Men's 3000 metres steeplechase\n|games = 1984 Summer\n|venue = [[Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum]]\n|dates = 3-6 August\n|competitors = 35\n|nations = 25\n|win_value = 8:11.80\n|longnames = yes\n|gold = [[Julius Korir]]\n|goldNOC = KEN\n|silver = [[Joseph Mahmoud]]\n|silverNOC = FRA\n|bronze = [[Brian Diemer]]\n|bronzeNOC = USA\n|prev = [[Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 3000 metres steeplechase|1980]]\n|next = [[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 3000 metres steeplechase|1988]]\n}}\n{{AthleticsAt1984SummerOlympics}}\n\nThe '''men's 3000 metres steeplechase''' at the [[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics|1984 Summer Olympics]] in [[Los Angeles, California]] had an entrylist of 35 competitors, with three qualifying heats (35 runners) and two semifinals (24) before the final (12) took place.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1984/ATH/mens-3000-metres-steeplechase.html |title=Athletics at the 1984 Los Angeles: Men's 3,000 metres Steeplechase |accessdate=25 November 2017 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\nDuring the first lap of the race, a bandit rushed the track, joining the race over the first water jump.  He managed to sprint past security over the next barrier and beyond before being tackled.  On the second lap, he managed to get free again for a few moments before finally being dragged away.\n{{quote|\"They've got all sorts of security at these games, designed to prevent anything from nuclear attack to germ warfare.  But the odd idiot is a real problem.\"|[[David Coleman]], [[BBC]] Commentator<ref>http://www.lescroupiersrunningclub.org.uk/forum/post/1783052</ref>}}\n\nShortly after the second lap began, [[Peter Renner]] assumed the lead, followed by Kenyan Julius duo of [[Julius Korir]] and [[Julius Kariuki]].  [[Henry Marsh (athlete)|Henry Marsh]] was typically as much as 20 metres back off the pace.  Renner opened up several metres on the Kenyans but with two laps to go, the field began bunching behind Renner with [[Brian Diemer]], [[Joseph Mahmoud]], [[Colin Reitz]] and Marsh back in the fold, all getting ready to pounce.  Just before the bell, Renner started to fall back.  Korir accelerated and Marsh was the first to follow, Diemer was next to catch up, followed by Mahmoud.  Through the final turn, Marsh looked like the only one still with any shot at Korir, but he was still losing ground.  Marsh was unable to make any headway as Mahmoud passed in on the outside, with Korir taking the final barrier as a hurdler and sprinting to victory.  Mahmoud sprinted away to the silver medal while Diemer challenged Marsh on the outside.  Diemer got the edge on Marsh with 10 metres to go, with the beaten Marsh just striding the final few steps over the line.\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|- \n|{{OlympicGoldMedalist|[[Julius Korir]]|KEN|1984 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicSilverMedalist|[[Joseph Mahmoud]]|FRA|1984 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicBronzeMedalist|[[Brian Diemer]]|USA|1984 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Abbreviations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"ccffcc\"| '''Q''' || automatic qualification\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"| '''q''' || qualification by rank\n|-\n|'''DNS''' || did not start\n|-\n|'''NM''' || no mark\n|-\n|'''OR''' || olympic record\n|-\n|'''WR''' || world record\n|-\n|'''AR''' || area record\n|-\n|'''NR''' || national record\n|-\n|'''PB''' || personal best\n|-\n|'''SB''' || season best\n|}\n\n==Records==\nThese were the standing world and Olympic records (in minutes) prior to the 1984 Summer Olympics.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|- \n! World Record\n| 8:05.4\n| {{flagicon|KEN}} [[Henry Rono]]\n| [[Seattle]] ([[United States|USA]])\n| May 13, 1978\n|-\n! Olympic Record\n| 8:08.02\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Anders G\u00e4rderud]]\n| [[Montreal]] ([[Canada|CAN]])\n| July 28, 1976\n|}\n\n==Final==\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"cccccc\"\n!RANK\n!align=\"center\" style=\"width: 20em\"|FINAL\n!align=\"center\" style=\"width: 5em\"|TIME\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 1.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Julius Korir]]|KEN|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:11.80'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 2.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Joseph Mahmoud]]|FRA|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:13.31'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 3.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Brian Diemer]]|USA|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:14.06'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|4.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Henry Marsh (athlete)|Henry Marsh]]|USA|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:14.25'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|5.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Colin Reitz]]|GBR|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:15.48'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|6.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Domingo Ram\u00f3n]]|ESP|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:17.27'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|7.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Julius Kariuki]]|KEN|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:17.47'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|8.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Pascal Debacker]]|FRA|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:21.51'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|9.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Tommy Ekblom]]|FIN|1984 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''8:23.95'''\n|-\n|align=\"center